I assume `DocumentUpload.FileContent` is a `Stream` - but I don&#39;t know what `DocumentUpload.PostedFile` is - but I assume `DocumentUpload.PostedFile.ContentLength` is an accurate measure of the length of `DocumentUpload.FileContent`.

1. You need to fully read the `FileContent` stream in a loop - not in a single `Read`call - or use a `MemoryStream`:
2. T-SQL parameters are used verbatim, not in quotes.
3. You&#39;re already using `using`, you don&#39;t need to close your `SqlConnection` manually.
4. You may need to close your `SqlCommand` too.
5. Do not use `AddWithValue`: https://blogs.msmvps.com/jcoehoorn/blog/2014/05/12/can-we-stop-using-addwithvalue-already/

Like so:

```
Int32 docLength = DocumentUpload.PostedFile.ContentLength;
Stream stream = DocumentUpload.FileContent;

Byte[] docBytes = new Byte[ docLength ];
{
    Int32 readSoFar = 0;
    while( readSoFar &lt; docLength )
    {
        Int32 remaining = docLength - readSoFar;
        Int32 read = stream.Read( docBytes, offset: readSoFar, count: remaining );
        if( read == 0 ) break;
        readSoFar += read;
    }
}

using( SqlConnection c = new SqlConnection( connectionString ) )
using( SqlCommand cmd = c.CreateCommand() )
{
    cmd.CommandText = &quot;INSERT INTO requests_table( [doc] ) VALUES( @docBytes )&quot;;
    cmd.Parameters.Add( new SqlParameter( &quot;@docBytes&quot;, SqlDbType.VarBinary, -1 ) { Value = docBytes } );
    
    c.Open();
    command.ExecuteNonQuery();
}
```

Alternatively, use `SqlBytes` if you want to forward the file-upload `Stream` which _may_ result in reduced memory usage (depending on how your `SqlClient` stack buffers data):

```
Stream stream = DocumentUpload.FileContent;

using( SqlConnection c = new SqlConnection( connectionString ) )
using( SqlCommand cmd = c.CreateCommand() )
{
    cmd.CommandText = &quot;INSERT INTO requests_table( [doc] ) VALUES( @docBytes )&quot;;
    cmd.Parameters.Add( new SqlParameter( &quot;@docBytes&quot;, SqlDbType.VarBinary, -1 ) { Value = new SqlBytes( stream ) } );
    
    c.Open();
    command.ExecuteNonQuery();
}
```

