I found out how. The `tf.GradientTape` class is designed to work within `with` block, ie. it has __enter__ and __exit__ methods. 

So to have it working outside &#39;with&#39; block, method `__enter__` must be explicitly called, however, avoid calling `__enter__` directly:

    x = tf.convert_to_tensor([1,2,3]);
    t = tf.GradientTape();
    t.__enter__();
    t.watch(x); 

